{"lemma":"حُبِّ","slug":"حُبِّ","root":"ح.ب.ب","root_slug":"ح-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حُبّ","root":"حبب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":17},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6839","n6845","n9402","n6846","n6847","n6848"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to love, to like","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give focus, to give attention","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be loved","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to love","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be loved","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَبَّ (ḥabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"love","tags":["rare"],"examples":[{"text":"وَتُحِبُّونَ الْمَالَ حُبًّا جَمًّا","english":"And you love wealth with abounding love."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"affection, attachment","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beloved, darling","tags":["rare"],"examples":[{"text":"وَمَا كُلُّ مَنْ يَهْوَى يَعِفُّ إِذَا خَلَا / عَفَافِي وَيُرْضِي ٱلْحِبَّ وَٱلْخَيْلُ تَلْتَقِي"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grains, seeds","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grain, cereal","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grains, kernels","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"granules","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pellets","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pills, pastilles","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"berries","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"acne, pustules, pimples","tags":["collective","rare"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħab.ba/","/ħub.ba/","/ħubb/","/ħibb/","/ħabb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6839","headword_ar":"حَبَّ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, loved, beloved, an object of love, affected, liked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habuba","text_ar":"حَبُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habiba","text_ar":"حَبِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a A_ilaY~a h`*aA Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"حَبَّ اـِلَىَّ هٰذَا الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This thing was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, an object of love to me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [The meaning is there indicated, but not expressed. In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aY'a","text_ar":"الشَّىءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habubotu A_ilayohi","text_ar":"حَبُبْتُ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I became loved, beloved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an object of love, to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[said to be] the only instance of its kind except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arurotu","text_ar":"شَرُرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labubotu","text_ar":"لَبُبْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kunota HabiybFA walaqado Habibota","text_ar":"مَا كُنْتَ حَبِيبًا وَلَقَدْ حَبِبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou wast not loved, and thou hast become loved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) See also 5. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a","text_ar":"حَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habuba","text_ar":"حَبُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by making the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent and incorporating it into the latter, is also a verb of praise [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beloved, lovely, pleasing, charming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent, is"},{"kind":"text","text":"he, or it]; (TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~a","text_ar":"حُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is more common,] formed from the same, by incorporating the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"into the latter after transferring the dammeh of the former to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISk, S, TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wazaAdahu kalafFA fiY AlHub~i A^ano manaEato\n                      \n                     \n                        waHab~a $ayoy^FA AlaY AlAnosaAni maA muniEaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And her denying increased his devotion in love: for lovely, as a thing, to man, is that which is denied"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And Sá'ideh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"hajarato gaDuwbu waHab~a mano yatajan~abu\n                      \n                     \n                        waEadato EawaAdK duwna waloyika ta$oEibu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ghadoob hath forsaken"},{"kind":"text","text":"thee, ("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and lovely is the person who withdraweth far away,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and obstacles in the way of thy drawing near have occurred to separate"},{"kind":"text","text":"thee and her]. (S, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a*aA","text_ar":"حَبَّذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] ―         -b3-  [Both are also verbs of wonder.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a bifulaAnK","text_ar":"حَبَّ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, and so in copies of the K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~a","text_ar":"حُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (I 'Ak p. 236, [where both forms are mentioned as correct,] and so in the CK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How beloved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lovely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K) to me! (As, S.) [See also 4.] A'Obeyd and Fr read this"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a","text_ar":"حَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", saying that it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habuba","text_ar":"حَبُبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bflAn","text_ar":"بفلان"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is rendered quiescent by the suppression of its dammeh, and incorporated into the latter. (S, * TA.)       -A2-  See also 4, in two places.       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a","text_ar":"حَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor., accord. to analogy,"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stood still, stopped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paused."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~a","text_ar":"حُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was fatigued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tired."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["As","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n6845","headword_ar":"حَبْ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabK","text_ar":"حَبٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cry by which a he-camel is chidden, to urge him on."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hawobi","text_ar":"حَوْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9402","headword_ar":"حَبْ","root":"Hwb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabK","text_ar":"حَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawobK","text_ar":"حَوْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6846","headword_ar":"حَبٌّ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) a [coll.] gen. n., (Msb,) n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~apN","text_ar":"حَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grain"},{"kind":"text","text":"of wheat, barley, lentils, rice, &c.: (Az, TA:) accord. to Ks, only of wheat and barley: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheat &c. while in the ears"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other envelopes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [but applied also to various other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"among which, to beans, (as in the Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bql","text_ar":"بقل"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and peas and the like; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kernels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"of grapes, dates, pomegranates, and the like: (Mgh voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EjamN","text_ar":"عجَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) by some it is applied even [to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"berries;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, for instance,] to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grapes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~apN","text_ar":"حَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino EinabK","text_ar":"مِنْ عِنَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Albur~i","text_ar":"مِنَ البُرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Al$~aEiyri","text_ar":"مِنَ الشَّعِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like: (TA:) [and hence, to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beads:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~N","text_ar":"حِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] the pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~N","text_ar":"حَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwbN","text_ar":"حُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~aAnN","text_ar":"حُبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tumoraAnN","text_ar":"تُمْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~apN","text_ar":"حَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~aAtN","text_ar":"حَبَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibaAbN","text_ar":"حِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~N","text_ar":"حَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also,] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbN","text_ar":"كِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobapN","text_ar":"كَلْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~N","text_ar":"حَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also called [by lexicologists, but not by grammarians,] a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~apN","text_ar":"حَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seed-produce,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether small or large. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHab~apu","text_ar":"الحَبَّةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaDoraA='u","text_ar":"الخَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbuTomu","text_ar":"البُطْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fruit of the terebinth-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pistacia terebinthus"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn. (Delile, Flor. Æg. no. 936.)] (K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHab~apu Als~awodaA='u","text_ar":"الحَبَّةُ السَّوْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uwniyzu","text_ar":"الشُّونِيزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The black aromatic seed of a species of nigella"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) [But see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swd","text_ar":"سود"},{"kind":"text","text":". And for other similar terms, see the latter word of each.] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a AlgamaAmi","text_ar":"حَبَّ الغَمَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~u Almuzoni","text_ar":"حَبُّ المُزْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~u qur~K","text_ar":"حَبُّ قُرٍّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hail."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. [See a metaphorical usage of the first of these in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~a","text_ar":"اَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b6-  [Hence likewise,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~N","text_ar":"حَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pimples,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small pustules:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the present day: and any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar small extuberances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a coll. gen. n.: n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":".] (S and K * in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hvr","text_ar":"حثر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Az","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n6847","headword_ar":"حُبٌّ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Love; affection;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wud~N","text_ar":"وُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"widaAdN","text_ar":"وِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclination of the nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural disposition, towards a thing that pleases,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delights;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 165;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bugoDN","text_ar":"بُغْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~N","text_ar":"حِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~apN","text_ar":"حُبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[this being said in the S to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in the K to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHab~apN","text_ar":"مَحَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and it is used as an inf. n. in an ex. cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAHN","text_ar":"دَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dwH","text_ar":"دوح"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubaAbN","text_ar":"حُبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibaAbN","text_ar":"حِبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHab~apN","text_ar":"مَحَبَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) signify the same; (S, K;) i. e., as above. (K.) The degrees of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~","text_ar":"حُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are as follow: first,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawFY","text_ar":"هَوًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", the “ inclining of the soul, or mind; ” also applied to the “ object of love itself: ” then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqapN","text_ar":"عَلَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ love cleaving to the heart; ” so termed because of the heart's cleaving to the object of love: then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalafN","text_ar":"كَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ violent, or intense, love; ” from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kulofapN","text_ar":"كُلْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ difficulty, or distress, or affliction: ” then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oqN","text_ar":"عِشْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [“ amorous desire; ” or “ passionate love; ”] in the S, “ excess of love; ” and in the language of the physicians, “ a kind of melancholy: ” then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$agafN","text_ar":"شَغَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ ardour of love, accompanied by a sensation of pleasure; ” like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawoEapN","text_ar":"لَوْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAEijN","text_ar":"لَاعِجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the former of which is “ ardour of love; ” and the latter, “ ardent love: ” then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawFY","text_ar":"جَوًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ inward love; ” and “ violence of amorous desire, ” or “ of grief, or sorrow: ” then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatay~umN","text_ar":"تَتَيُّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ a state of enslavement by love: ” then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabolN","text_ar":"تَبْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ lovesickness: ” then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walahN","text_ar":"وَلَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ distraction, or loss of reason, in love: ” and then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huyaAmN","text_ar":"هُيَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ a state of wandering about at random in consequence of overpowering love. ” (Kull ubi suprà.) [Accord. to the Msb, it is a simple subst.: but accord. to the K, an inf. n.; and hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~FA limaA A^aHobabotumo","text_ar":"حُبًّا لِمَا اَحْبَبْتُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHib~u Hub~FA","text_ar":"اُحِبُّ حُبًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I love with loving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much, what ye have loved"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 186.) Hence the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wakaraAmapF","text_ar":"وَكَرَامَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEamo waHub~apF","text_ar":"نَعَمْ وَحُبَّةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Yea; and with love and honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"will I do what thou requirest: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the sake of"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"love and honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"that I bear thee: or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hb~p","text_ar":"حبّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be here used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~FA","text_ar":"حُبًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"to assimilate it in termination to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"krAmp","text_ar":"كرامة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see what follows]. (S, TA.) Hence also the saying of Abu-l-' Atà EsSindee,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fawaA@ll~`hi maA A^adoriY waA_in~iY laSaAdiqN\n                      \n                     \n                        A^adaA='N EaraAniY mino HubaAbiki A^amo siHoru"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And by God, I know not"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and indeed I am speaking truth"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether disease have befallen me in consequence of love of thee, or enchantment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) but IB says that the reading best known is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino HibaAbiki","text_ar":"مِنْ حِبَابِكِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibAb","text_ar":"حِباب"},{"kind":"text","text":", here, may be an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAbabotuhu","text_ar":"حَابَبْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or it may be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$A$N","text_ar":"عِشاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$~N","text_ar":"عُشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) or it may be an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hababotuhu","text_ar":"حَبَبْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": some also read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino HabaAbiki","text_ar":"مِنْ حَبَابِكِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":", said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on account of the love of thee, and of the main amount thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 26:) and some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino janaAbiki","text_ar":"مِنْ جَنَابِكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ from thy part ” [or “ from thee ”]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiybN","text_ar":"حَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also a Persian word, arabicized, (AHát, S, Msb,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunob","text_ar":"خُنْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHát, TA,) [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubo","text_ar":"خُبْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuPo","text_ar":"خُپْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAbiyapN","text_ar":"خَابِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A jar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, MF,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether large or small, used for preparing wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large jar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one for water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four pieces of wood upon which is placed a two-handled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two-eared, jar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA: [in the CK, by a misplacement of words, this last signification is assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAb","text_ar":"حَبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaAbN","text_ar":"اَحْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibaAbN","text_ar":"حِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibabapN","text_ar":"حِبَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) From this last signification is [said to be] derived the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~FA wakaraAmapF","text_ar":"حُبًّا وَكَرَامَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~FA wakaraAmaho","text_ar":"حُبًّا وَكَرَامَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A jarstand and a cover"},{"kind":"text","text":"will I give thee, or the like],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"krAmp","text_ar":"كرامة"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the “ cover ” of a jar, (K, TA,) whether of wood or of baked clay. (TA.) [If this be the true derivation, the phrase may have originated from a person's asking of another the loan or gift of a jar, and the latter's replying “ Yea; and I will give thee a jar-stand and a cover; ” meaning “ I will do what thou requirest, and more: ” but this phrase is now, and perhaps was in early times, generally used, agreeably with the more common significations of the two words, in the sense assigned above to the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~apF","text_ar":"حُبَّةً"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wakaraAmapF","text_ar":"وَكَرَامَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["A","Mgh","TA","S","K","Msb","MF","IDrd"]},{"entry_id":"n6848","headword_ar":"حِبٌّ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiybN","text_ar":"حَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places:       -A2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~apN","text_ar":"حِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibaAbN","text_ar":"حِبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but the latter is doubted by the author of the TA, and thought to be perhaps syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hib~N","text_ar":"حِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHib~N","text_ar":"مُحِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the L it is said to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hb~N","text_ar":"حبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but in"},{"kind":"page_break","n":497},{"kind":"text","text":"what sense is not explained,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ear-ring"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"formed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~ap","text_ar":"حَبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bead"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}